ğŸ“œâœ”ï¸ğŸ”´ğŸ”´ğŸ”´CONTROL FLOW of PROGRAM ğŸ”´ğŸ”´ğŸ”´
âœ”ï¸ Computer do ONLY 1 Thing 
_ğŸ“œ_From START to shutdown, a CPU simply READS & EXECUTES ( INTERRUPT's) a SEQUENCE of INSTRUCTIONS, ONE at a TIME.
mtlb PROGRAM COUNTER INCREAMENT hunda REHNDA te CPU next INSTRUCTIONS fetch krda rehnda ohna de OPERAND de hisab nal MEMORY ACCESS krda te COMPUTATION's krda___THIS IS BASICALLY WHAT CPU KEEP's on DOING FOREVER UNTIL we SHUT IT DOWN
ğŸ“œğŸ“œâœ”ï¸ ALTERING THE CONTROL FLOW OF PROGRAM & HOW MANY METHODS ARE AVAILABLE & HOW TO REACH/ENTER OPERATING SYSTEM ğŸ“œ
ğŸ”´âœ”ï¸2 BASIC method for the program to change/alter control flow UNDER HIS OWN CONTROL
