ğŸ“œâœ”ï¸ğŸ“œ TYPES of EXCEPTION's
ğŸ”´ Definition= An EXCEPTION is a TRANSFER of CONTROL to the [ OS ] in response to some EVENT(change in PROCESSOR state)jdo v program de current state ch EXCEPTION occur hoi ta [ OS ] ch CONTROL gea & [ OS ] PROCESS exception  te fir CONTROL RETURN hogea NEXT INSTRUCTION nu / ja [ OS ] CONTROL program nu kre
ğŸ”´ INTERRUPT'S == caused by event external to the PROCESSOR & these are indicated by setting the PROCESSOR INTERRUPT PIN 
